text.tspan: Drag the blue corners of the rectangles below to understand
how it affects the current diagram,
Each black square represents a rectangle.
Any time a rectangle is completely inside another, an arrow is added
between the two corresponding dots, unless the smaller rectangle is
inside an intermediate rectangle that is inside the bigger rectangle.
On a given row, the black squares are ordered according
to the x then y coordinates of the corresponding rectangles.
Vertically, the black squares are placed proportionally to the length
of the longest path between them and one of their ancestors.
